From {{inh|en|enm|Èerde}}, {{m|enm|yerd}}, {{m|enm|Èerd}}, from {{der|en|ang|Ä¡ierd||[[branch]]; [[rod]], [[staff]]; [[measuring]] [[stick]]; [[yardland]]}}, from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*gaÊ€d}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*gazdaz}}. Cognate with {{cog|nl|gard||twig}}, {{cog|de|Gerte}} and probably related to Latin {{m|la|hasta||[[spear]]}}.<ref>''Oxford English Dictionary'', 1st ed. "yard, ''n.<sup><small>2</small></sup>''". Oxford University Press (Oxford), 1921.</ref>
